{
  "doc_id": "22938",
  "text": "The existing datasets [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] are not suitable for use in evaluating our framework to recognize the object-related actions in real-world scenes for two reasons. First, the existing datasets for skeleton-based action recognition were captured in constrained environments. These datasets acquired from sensors are limited to indoor environments. Therefore, the constrained datasets are insufficient for modeling realistic scenes because these datasets cover only a few variations in dynamic environments. Second, these datasets usually include one actor in each image, which is not reflective of the scenes from real-world surveillance. In our evaluation, instead of using the existing datasets, we use two realistic datasets captured in unconstrained real-world environments, which contain only raw video clips without skeleton data. The two datasets are described below.",
